{"lemma":"شَرْعُ","slug":"شَرْعُ","root":"ش.ر.ع","root_slug":"ش-ر-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ر-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"شَرْعُ","root":"شرع","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":19},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n22135","n22136","n22137"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%B9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to prescribe a road to walk upon or a law to follow, to lead, to give laws"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have an outlet into the street"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to publish"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be open and distinct"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to strip the skin"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lift very high"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to go (into the water)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to engage in a business, to begin"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make ready for"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be straight"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to stretch the neck"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to mark or show the way distinctly"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to open a path"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lead the cattle to the most convenient watering place"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make clear"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lift up"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of شَرَعَ (šaraʕa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"synonym of الشَّرِيعَة (aš-šarīʕa, “the shari'a”)","tags":["definite"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of شِرَاع (širāʕ)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22135","headword_ar":"شَرْعٌ","root":"$rE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", originally an inf. n.: ―         -b2-  then applied as a name for"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A manifest, a plain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an open, track,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"road,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way:"},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b3-  and then, metaphorically, to The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"divine way of religion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so says Er-Rághib; (TA;) syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariyEapN","text_ar":"شَرِيعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. (Msb.) ―         -b4-  In the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mararotu birajulK $aroEika","text_ar":"مَرَرْتُ بِرَجُلٍ شَرْعِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mrrt","text_ar":"مررت"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"birajulK $aroEuka mino rajulK","text_ar":"بِرَجُلٍ شَرْعُكَ مِنْ رَجُلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the S and O, [for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa $aroEuka","text_ar":"هُوَ شَرْعُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) with kesr and with damm to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E","text_ar":"ع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$rEk","text_ar":"شرعك"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (TA,) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I passed by a man"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sufficing thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as a man"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, O, K,) the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sort to which thou directest thyself and which thou seekest"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhi wataTolubuhu","text_ar":"فِيهِ وَتَطْلُبُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta$oraEu","text_ar":"تَشْرَعُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (S, O:) and the word in this sense is used alike as sing. and pl. (S, O, K) and dual, because it is [originally] an inf. n. (S, O.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aroEuka h`*aA","text_ar":"شَرْعُكَ هٰذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aAni","text_ar":"هٰذَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`w^ulaA='i","text_ar":"هٰوُلَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sufficient for thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is this"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are these two"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are these"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S: and the like is said in the Mgh.) And it is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"$aroEuka maA bal~agaka AlmaHal~aA"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus correctly, for it is a hemistich; not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaHal~a","text_ar":"المَحَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the S and K; (TA;) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sufficient"},{"kind":"text","text":"travel-ling-provision"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for thee is that which will cause thee to reach the place"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of alighting"},{"kind":"text","text":"] to which thou repairest: (K, TA:) applied to the case of being content with little. (S, K.) ―         -b5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$araEN","text_ar":"شَرَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b6-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iroEapN","text_ar":"شِرْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["TA","S","O","K"]},{"entry_id":"n22136","headword_ar":"شِرْعٌ","root":"$rE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aroE","text_ar":"شَرْع"},{"kind":"text","text":",] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iroEapN","text_ar":"شِرْعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) [but the former is masc. and ↓ the latter is fem.; for] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA $iroEu h`*aA","text_ar":"هٰذَا شِرْعُ هٰذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is the like of this;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iroEapu","text_ar":"شِرْعَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aAni $iroEaAni","text_ar":"هٰذَانِ شِرْعَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"these two are likes."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA.) [The pls., or rather coll. gen. ns. and pls., following this meaning in the K belong to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iroEapN","text_ar":"شِرْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aroEapN","text_ar":"شَرْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in another sense; as is shown by exs. in the O and TA.]       -A2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chords of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barobaT","text_ar":"بَرْبَط"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K, TA,) which is the ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Persian"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euwd","text_ar":"عُود"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lute"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [In this sense, a coll. gen. n.:] see its n. un."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iroEapN","text_ar":"شِرْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  And hence, as being likened thereto, (TA,) (tropical:)  The ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thong called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iraAk","text_ar":"شِرَاك"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a sandal."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA.) It is related in a trad. that a man said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~iY A^uHib~u AljamaAla Hat~aY fiY $iroEi naEoliY","text_ar":"اـِنِّى اُحِبُّ الجَمَالَ حَتَّى فِى شِرْعِ نَعْلِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA) i. e. (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily I love elegance, even"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$rAk","text_ar":"شراك"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of my sandal."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","O"]},{"entry_id":"n22137","headword_ar":"شَرَعٌ","root":"$rE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariyEapN","text_ar":"شَرِيعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAsu fiY h`*aA","text_ar":"النَّاسُ فِى هٰذَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^amori $araEN","text_ar":"الاَمْرِ شَرَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aroEN","text_ar":"شَرْعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) the latter a contraction of the former, (Msb,) allowed by Kr and Kz, but disallowed by Yaakoob, (IDrst, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people are in this affair equals:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K:) in this sense, used alike as sing. and pl. and fem. (S, TA) and masc.: (TA:) [of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$araEN","text_ar":"شَرَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] Az says that it seems to be pl. [or quasi-pl. n.] of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAriEN","text_ar":"شَارِعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadamN","text_ar":"خَدَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAdimN","text_ar":"خَادِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; i. e., [the phrase means]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the people enter into this affair"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ya$oraEuwna fiyhi","text_ar":"يَشْرَعُونَ فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"together."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAsu $araEN waAHidN","text_ar":"النَّاسُ شَرَعٌ وَاحِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wAHd","text_ar":"واحد"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aroEN","text_ar":"شَرْعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people are one sort."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","IDrst","TA"]}]}}